<h1> Learn Ruby The Hard Way </h1>

<h2> How do I start? </h2>
<p> Go to homework assignments </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>cd ~/workspace/davinici_coders_*class session*_*class year*/homework_assignments </output>
<p> Making directory lrthw_exercises </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>mkdir lrthw_exercises</output>
<p> Go into the directory </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>cd lrthw_exercises</output>
<p> Set up RVM to load version '2.1.2' for this directory </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>echo '2.1.2' > .ruby-version</output>
<p> Set up RVM to load gemsets for this directory </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>echo 'lrthw_exercise' > .ruby-gemset </output>
<p> Reload RVM setting </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>cd .</output>
<p> Load current directory in RubyMine </p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<output> >>mine .</output>
<h2> How do I set up Rubocop for lrthw? </h2>
<p> Go to Gemfile set up sources and gems, then bundle and run</p>
<!--<button>Hint</button>-->
<p> In RubyMine/Gemfile</p>
<pre>
  Source 'http://rubygems.org'

  gem 'guard-rubocop'
</pre>
<p>Then go to Terminal, type in the following:</p>
<pre>
  >>bundle
  >>guard init
  >>guard
</pre>
